<title>GERMANY: Beta Systems says IPO offering range 85-100 marks.</title>
<headline>Beta Systems says IPO offering range 85-100 marks.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1997-06-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>German software group Beta Systems said on Monday that shares for its initial public offering will be priced between 85 and 100 marks in a bookbuilding process.</p>
<p>Beta Systems will offer up to 897,000 shares, each with a a nominal value of five marks.</p>
<p>A &quot;greenshoe option,&quot; which would allow additional shares to be sold if demand were strong, was set at 117,000 shares, the company said at a news conference.</p>
<p>More than 70 percent of the shares come from a capital rights measure.</p>
<p>The bookbuilding phase will last through June 26 and a final price for the offering will be set on that day.</p>
<p>Pricing on the German bourse is set for June 30.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
